hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The bed, the pillows and bed linens were comfortable. Sharing a triple room with my daughter & niece was tight but doable. The sleeper chair was very squeaky & though there was a tiny lift, there were some stairs to climb. We were on the 4th floor. I would not recommend to anyone elderly.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Very nice hotel. The rooms are comfortable, great location, friendly staff and delicious breakfast. Great location to explore Paris from with really nice local food shops to grabs quick bites from right around the hotel. We would stay here again if we find ourselves back in Paris!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This was our first time in Paris and the concierge, Sam, was extremely helpful during our stay. The hotel is conveniently located in a nice and quiet area yet so close to everything. We also recommend the breakfastâ€”it was very good!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Cozy room, (but no elevator to 1st floor). It's in a great area that is close to good restaurants. Very safe walking to our destinations. Desk staff very helpful with our many questions. We would definitely stay there again.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Room: Booked a single room and was pleasantly surprised that despite the small room size, the room interior was cozy and soothing with well planned layout and equipped with all basic amenities; desk, closet, kettle, coffee and tea station. The bed was comfortable. (As comparison, the room size is more spacious and comfortable than the size of single bed hotel room in Tokyo). The slight point to note is the bathroom which could be slightly cramp for a person with larger built.

Location: Good location. 7-10 mins walk to Eiffel Towel, 5 mins to Metro.

Hospitality: Knowledgeable and helpful staff. They have guided me on transportation and restaurants.

Breakfast with fair selection of bread, cold cuts, cheese and egg, particularly the warm croissant.

Tip: Would recommend to opt for breakfast for Sunday as the breakfast restaurant nearby may not be opened on Sunday in Paris. Restaurant nearby: Do dine at Arnold Nicolas (in Michelin's Guide) which is a stone's throw away for its set menu, terrine and charcuterie. Les Cocottes serves go escargot with bread.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
My family stayed here at the end of March. The hotel is located on a very quiet street with lots of food options nearby. The Eiffel Tower is a short, easy walk away. The location is perfect.
The room is small, but we knew that before visiting. It is comfortable with decent in-room storage considering the size. It wasn't a problem for us on our short stay. They have pack-n-plays (crib) and high chairs available which was greatly appreciated. Due to the size of the room, we didn't end up using the pack-n-play but appreciated it being available and setup in our room at arrival.
The hotel staff was very friendly and helpful.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The rooms were super clean and comfortable and the hotel is in a great location near Rue Cler and walking distance to the Eiffel Tower. The concierge, Sam, was an absolute gentleman and incredibly nice. He saw my elderly mother struggles with getting around and changed her to a room on the first floor with a more accessible and larger bathroom. He stored our bags for us while we waited for our rooms to be ready. I highly recommend this hotel.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
My pre-teen daughter and I stayed here for a spring break trip. This hotel is excellent. I wanted to let you know what a great time we had and it was made all the better by the gracious and helpful staff and the location and feel of the hotel. Some of the highlights of the hotel:
1) Zied helped us with everything and was so nice. He checked in with us before we left and gave us lots of helpful tips. He also worked with us when I had made a mistake in booking and made sure we got an extra night.
2) This is a small intimate hotel (my guess is no more than 20 rooms). While the rooms are small compared to large chain hotels, it was wonderful in that you got to know some of the guests and desk staff.
3) On site breakfast was a plus. While there are lots of great little cafes and restaurants all on the same block, it was good to grab some coffee and croissants before heading out.
4) Very clean!
5) Great location. It is a few blocks from the Eiffel Tower on a small pedestrian street. It is also just a few blocks from the metro, Rail station, and bus lines.

Some things to consider:
1) The rooms are small, like most older Paris hotels. If you are a heavy packer or need a lot of bathroom space, you might want to consider a chain hotel.
2) If you have mobility issues, I would think this hotel might be a difficult one for you. They call Paris the city of Lights, but I would call it the city of stairs! This hotel is no different. Lots of tiny winding stairs to your room. There is a small elevator, but you enter and exit in the middle of the winding staircase, so you still have to navigate 7-9 stairs.
3) The breakfast is not big buffet style. It is coffee, tea, juice, water, breads, boiled eggs, a meat and cheese tray, yogurt, and cereal. I thought it was great, but if you are a big eater, maybe consider that before purchase.

Overall this is a wonderful hotel and the staff really put it over the top. I would 100% recommend it.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Staff very friendly and helpful!
Great location! You can walk to the Eiffel Tower. The restaurants around the hotel were delicious. Their is a convenient store on the main street from the hotel, very sweet man and helpful.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
This hotel is in a great location. There are multiple Michelin restaurants, one street over from it. Even the restaurants that aren't Michelin stars are really great.

It is in a really safe and convenient place. There are fromageries, patisseries, boulangeries, markets, and chocolatiers all around the hotel. Despite so many businesses close-by, it is very quiet: unbelievably quiet.

The three monsieurs at reception were cheerful and helpful.

Breakfast was fresh and plentyful.

Now, for the Americans out there, the rooms and elevator are probably much smaller than you will expect. However, you'll be located in one of the safest and most convenient parts of Paris, a 5-10 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower, and 5-10 minutes to the metro. You'll quickly forget about the size of the room.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Overall is perfect. Only there is limited space of the room for 3 pax. The elevator is very slim and had no landing area for baggage during awaiting the elevator, have to standby on stairway which might a fall risk.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
I stayed with a friend in July 2022 for one week and we had a really good timeâ€¦.
The hotel is clean , the people were very nice and the food was amazing.
Very good location with many things to do around
Will come back again with pleasure !!!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Wow just wow
From the moment we walked in we were greeted with a warm welcome and big smile.
Zied was amazing
His attention to detail with his passion for service was fantastic
No question or request was to big or too small
Zied went out of his way to make our stay comfortable
Thank you to you and your team Zied
We will definitely be back.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: My time at the Hotel Malte was enjoyable. The staff is incredibly kind and helpful, the location is great, and I thought the price was fair. The difference was created by little things like the complimentary mini bar, the free wifi, and the renewing supply of pastries and coffee in the lobby.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: this hotel is so fancy that my family want to visit again, it's so very clean and neat. the service is very approachable and understanding. we loved it i recommend this hotel for everyone who wants to stay.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Even with pandemic touching my feet, all the staff was very kind and helpful to let me have a wonderful stay. Every breakfast were delicious and with french style always. I felt like a little french-latin girl starting everyday with it

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: If you are looking to stay walking distance to the Eiffel Tower and close the the main attractions this location is perfect!! It was clean and had all the basics that we needed. So many great shops and restaurants right outside the hotel. Zied at the front desk was SO helpful and friendly, he made me and my friend feel welcomed and went above and beyond!! Highly recommend this hotelðŸ‘ðŸ½

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The rooms are very small, bathroom sink the size of the airline toilet but the worst was the elevator and stairs. That setup is an accident waiting to happen. Except for the excellent staff which are professional and friendly, I will not recommend this place. Sorry

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Went to Paris and wanted a good location for a reasonable rate. This hit the mark perfectly. The staff was absolutely incredible helping us get tickets, print vouchers, get a cab to train station etc. Everything we needed they helped. The rooms in Paris are small and this was no exception, but we knew this and it was fine. Comfy bed and the elevator was a saviour for our luggage. A very nice stay, would visit again for sure.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Indeed a very small room, but to be expected in the middle of the city, and very clean. Walking distance to the Eiffel Tower and Rue Cler. The men at the front desk were very friendly and welcoming. It was also a short walk to the metro, plus many little grocery and (not so tacky) souvenir stores on the adjacent street.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Wonderful stay HÃ´tel de La Paix Tour Eiffel in Paris. The staff was great and helped us contacting the airline who lost our luggage (Aer Lingus). The location is good with a bunch of nice shops and restaurants within a couple of blocks; 20 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. The hotel also offers a breakfast which was pretty good.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The hotel was very cute and clean, and the front desk people - particularly Zied (sp?) - were super nice and helpful. They have a tiny elevator that doesn't QUITE take you to the floor you want - you still have to walk up a few stairs - so if you're a person with a disability, that could be an issue. The hotel is well-located with tons of restaurants around, and the Eiffel Tower just a few blocks away. The bed is small but SUPER comfortable. I would definitely stay there again. Thanks!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: I stayed just one night and I was traveling alone, but when I checked in they were so friendly and welcoming I felt comfortable. I was a bit surprised at the small size of the single room, but it was super clean and had everything I needed. I did not make it for the breakfast as I had some changes to my flight and decided to sleep in, but I regret that as I think it would have been very nice! In the morning the gentleman that worked the front desk (I did not get anyoneâ€™s name) was so accommodating and called me a taxi as I was having trouble with my Uber app. I would definitely recommend this hotel for the service and quaintness of the place!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Outstanding! Quiet, comfortable and the employees very friendly and supportive. Breakfast was dekicious. Staff helped with securing cabs and giving directions. The Hotel is only minutes from the Eidel tower!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Great spot right off a main road . Close to the Eiffel Tower , lots of great cafes and food stores nearby . Staff were all exceptionally helpful and kind . Absolutely recommend ! I plan to say here again when I come for my second visit next summer . ðŸ˜ŠðŸ‘

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Great location, lovely staff, very clean room with ac and delicious breakfast! As a solo traveller I definitely recommend this hotel. Hotel staff was very helpful with everything that you may need. Very close to eiffel tower. Reception is open 24/7.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: We had two rooms for five days. The hotel is tranquil and in a great location. The Eiffel tower is a five-minute walk. There are numerous restaurants, and cafe's within walking distance. Zied was amazing!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: We enjoyed our stay at this hotel! Very quiet and clean. The rooms are small, so we booked two rooms for our family of four. Conveniently located near the Eiffel Tower. We also enjoyed being so close to Rue Cler street with many great food options! Would definitely stay here again.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
The staff was amazing and sooooo helpful.
Sam and Zied and another gentleman (whose name I don't want to botch) were very great hosts. The hotel is small. But i understand that is normal for Paris. My room was better suited for a couple and small luggages.
It is very close to the Eiffel tower. The neighborhood is safe and located within walking distance of restaurants, self wash and a convenience store.
Breakfast is available, it was included in my price.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
This was my last hotel of 5 that I stayed in on my solo trip to France.
The location was EXCELLENT! 5 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower, including lots of places to eat and shop.
10 minute walk to the Musee de L'Armee (their night show is amazing!) and Cafe L'Esplanade, as well as so many other popular placed.
There is staff 24 hours at the front desk. They were all very friendly and helpful.
The breakfast was included with my stay and was Excellent! - yogurt, eggs, cheeses, meats, croissants, fruit, cakes, juices, hot chocolate, and more!
My room was tiny but just right for me. The bed was very comfortable, with lots of soft, fluffy pillows.
The bathroom was a bit of a tight fit, but very clean and modern. There were no toiletries, but I had brought my own anyway. Lots of towels which were thick and soft.
Tiny elevator (which I found in all the hotels in France), but I was on the 3rd floor and preferred to walk the spiral staircase.
Very quiet - I did not hear any other guests at all (but did see them at breakfast, so it was not because it was empty - lol).
And there is A/C which is very important in the summer in Paris!
I definitely recommend this hotel. :D

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: It was a good hotel close to everything. Very clean and the breakfast was good. The only negative I can give is that our room were too small and the AC kept switching off during the night. The staff was amazing and very helpful and the check in was so quick.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Great place. Very clean, great location, friendly staff and nicely decorated. Small room, but it was great for a couple day visit. Just blocks from Eiffel Tower and a short walk to the metro. Would definitely return.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
My son loved the hotel bc of the cool lights and technology options. It was close to the airport which was nice. Room was clean and food options were nice.

My son left his iPad in the room and they are kind enough to help get it back to the States.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This was a small but nice boutique hotel. The shower was extremely small. Staff extremely nice & helpful, especially Zieb! From the first time I emailed with questions about the area, etc they responded almost instantly. Speaking only English, this was extremely helpful. Our luggage was lost & Zieb went over & above to help us track it down.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This hotel was a great experience! They were so helpful and provided a survey before I arrived with help. This is a great little hotel in a quaint neighborhood and close enough to walk to the Eiffel Tower and Seine River. Stay here! It's so great!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Maybe a 5 minute walk to tower. Front desk was helpful. It's hard to find rooms in Paris that hold 3 people. Our room was quaint, but perfect for us. Good sleep quality. Lots of restaurants nearby. Avoid the ones closest to tower.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Arrival

The hotel is half a block down a pedestrian alley so expect the taxi to drop you off a short distance from the front door. There was one person behind the front desk and no other attendants that I could see.

Check In
Was smooth and friendly. We got into our room earlier than expected which was welcome. Front desk people were very friendly and helpful on our stay.

Lift/Elevator
It's small even by European standards. It also has a weight limit of 180kg. We went one at a time with one bag each.

Stairs
There is a circular stairway from the basement to the top floor. It's easy to navigate and helps with the aesthetic. Only problem is that it stops at a very very narrow landing between each floor. If you have bags it's better to go a floor higher and carry the bag down. Be careful not to fall when the lift opens.

Room
There were two of us in a small room. We had a narrow view of the street but nothing special. The room was extremely small. There was hardly any room to put one suitcase much less two. And the bathroom was tiny. The room and bathroom were smaller than any of the cruise ship cabins I've stayed in.

Breakfast
The free buffet started at 630a. It was usually empty but there are plenty of tables. Food included fresh croissants, fruit cups, coffee machine, fruit juice, ham/salami/cheese, etc. Everything was fresh and tasty. It was a nice place to start the morning.

Neighborhood
We felt like we lived in Paris. There were restaurants and shops all around -- shops for people who lived there not for tourists. Bus and Metro stops were also convenient. We mostly ate in the neighborhood and didn't feel at all crowded by the hoards of tourists at all the tourist spots.

Tour Eiffel
We chose this place because it was a five minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. That was definitely worth it. But we also loved the neighborhood.

Language
Everyone in the hotel spoke English and probably many other languages.

Noise
The walls are thin.

Conclusion
Low cost, convenient place in a friendly neighborhood with great staff.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
The booking and communications with hotel were on point! Sam provided helpful details on which train stations to take upon arrival to Gare du Nord. We booked our Eiffel Tower, Louvre & Toot Bus through site with no problems.

Room and breakfast were lovely, staff was always friendly, and the location...I mean it is perfect in a great part of town with access to activities and food. Loved it!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Beautiful place to stay just an 8 minute stroll to the Eiffel Tower. Delicious breakfast and excellent customer service with kind and very helpful staff. Great restaurants right outside your door! We will definitely return

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: I really liked it here. We had some trouble with the shower leaking and they fixed it immediately. There was some confusion with flat sheets which I guess isn't done in France. Thankfully my mom had seen they had some when we went to breakfast so they gave us some. I would stay here again if I came back.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Fantastic location round the corner from the Eiffel Tower. 4 minute walk to the metro, 30 mins in a taxi/metro to Gare du Nord. Lots of lovely cafe's and restaurants nearby. I checked a number of reviews before I booked and many rated highly on the cleanliness which is a big thing for me. I was not disappointed, very clean, modern bathrooms, comfortable bed. Rooms are relatively small but didn't feel cramped - I guess the only downside is the walls are quite thin so you can hear other people chatting in adjacent rooms/hallways. However I think this is pretty common in Paris. Air con and large windows that open which is great for fresh air/temp control. Fantastic, friendly and welcoming reception staff who found a room for me when I had issues with the Eurostar and had to stay an additional night. Will definitely be staying here again. Thanks so much :)

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Lovely small hotel a short walk from the Eiffel Tower. Our Covid avoidance strategy was to walk to as many museums and attractions as we could, rather than going into the Metro. This hotel was a mile or less from the important museums. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Room was quite small (it's Paris) but very well furnished, good bed. Breakfast was good. Nice restaurants nearby. Recommended.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Two of my friends and I recently stayed at the Hotel De La Paix Tour Eiffel in the heart of Paris. The hotel has the most wonderful atmosphere and the men at the front desk are so friendly and helpful. The hotel is located in a wonderful area near to the Eiffel Tower and on a small, winding street with sidewalk cafes nearby. The breakfast that the hotel offers is also excellent. I would definitely stay there if I am ever lucky enough to visit Paris again.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This hotel is in a very good location. It's close to the Eiffel Tower, Rue Cler and many good restaurants. We found the front desk staff to be excellent. Always friendly and helpful! The room was small but that's pretty typical of older European hotels. We would definitely stay again!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: We had a fantastic stay at this boutique hotel. Our room was off in a private area which we enjoyed immensely. The location is great for walking around. There are lots of food options. The front desk went above and beyond in their help. Upon arriving we realized we had a problem with a tour we had booked. Zied was on the phone immediately and got that squared away for us. We also needed to ship some items home and he helped fill out all the paperwork that was needed. I can not express my thanks for his help with items that could have caused me stress and were outside of the normal concierge duties. Thank you from the bottom of my heart. You made my much anticipated return to Paris perfect.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: I was at this hotel last week in a single room, and really enjoyed my experience!! Of course, the hotel is small, and my room was very small... but who is staying inside the room while on a trip to Paris!?! The bed was comfortable, shower had hot water and good water pressure, breakfast was simple but delicious, and overall -everything was clean, and very nice. But the best part of my experience by far was the charming and kind front desk host named Zied. From the moment I arrived until he arranged my taxi to the airport, he was extremely helpful. He called me by name, ensured everything was to my liking, smiled and chatted many times, and made my short stay feel personal and wonderful. I would definitely stay at this hotel again!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
I've stayed at HÃ´tel de La Paix Tour Eiffel several times, usually once or twice per year for several days.

Just flew in from the US and tried to check in - no reservation in my name. I booked thru Hotels.com for 4 days.

I did show up late, took 20 hours to get to Paris. Because I was late they cancelled my entire stay. Told me I needed to call and let them know. Easier said than done when traveling.

They had already rebooked my rooms. So here I am, no sleep to speak of for a day, with no room in Paris.

The Hotel clerk did agree to call Hotels.com and get me a refund for all but one night (out about $250).

Ended up in a dump that looks like a Motel 6 behind a New Jersey truck stop,

You be the judge on this one......

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Terrible service, small and smelly rooms, and the shower leaked into the bedroom. The front deal clerk was so rude and incompetent. Changed hotel rooms the next day. This was very disappointing but our new hotel was so worth the hassle.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: I had a fantastic stay at Hotel de la Paix! I had spent a couple days at Disneyland with my family, and then needed to find a great hotel for my one solo day in the city of Paris. I made a great choice! The staff was very friendly and helpful! They assisted in checking in early, and helped me book a car to the airport. The room was nice and clean, and the hotel is very conveniently located! I was able to walk everywhere. Eiffel Tower, Rue Cler (great cafes), Louvre, Saint-Germain area, etc. all within walking distance! Merci! -Katie Anne

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Nice , but very small rooms and bathrooms, good breakfast, not noisy from the street, but you can hear your neighbourâ€¦..the distance to eiffeltower ist perfect, many restaurants in the surroundings. Perfect for a sightseeing weekend!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Upon our arrival to the hotel, we received a warm welcome and all our questions about our stay and the area were answered. The room was quaint, and exceptionally clean. Breakfast was a perfect start each morning. We would stay here again.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Great customer services all Front Desk agents was amazing and exceptional in customer service the hotel cleanness was perfect mire than excellent location breakfast was just perfect. I'll definitely book this hotel again

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Stayed here with my family for 1 night in flying visit to Paris. Clean little hotel with amazing staff, they were always friendly and helpful with any advice I needed about getting around etc..location perfect, cafes and restaurants are nearby and best of all 5 minutes walk to Eiffel Tower. Would definitely stay again and will recommend to anyone whoâ€™s going Paris.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Hotel de la Paix gave me such a warm welcoming when I arrived in Paris after an overnight flight from the US. I arrived early in the morning and I was greeted cheerfully. My room wasn't ready yet but the man at the front desk recommended a wonderful coffee shop around the corner. The staff there was friendly and accommodating, too! They kept my luggage while I went out and explored the city.
I loved my room. I had the solo traveler single room. It was small but adorable and had everything I needed. Clean, modern, and very comfortable. The only thing that wasn't the best was the noise in the hallway and on the stairs. Lots of other guests coming and going, so it was a bit loud and hard to sleep. The breakfast was simple but wonderful. The pain au chocolat was warm and delicious, probably the best I had during my stay in France. I would definitely stay here agin.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Loved this hotel! Super clean and the staff here is so friendly and pleasant. Best part of the hotel was the location. It was a 5-10 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower and close to several restaurants and bakeries. I would definitely come stay here again!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Extreamly clean hotel & very nice staff. Close to Eiffle Tower. Plenty of resteraunts nearby & easy access to subways to see all sites Paris has to offer. Had an adjoining room since there was four of us.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Hotel is located 5 minutes away from the Eiffel Tower, I want to give a special shout to to Sam, he was kind enough to help me set up my SIM card as I had no clue, he went above and beyond to help me out. The place is super clean and looks very modern.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: I loved staying at this hotel for my first stay in Paris. Itâ€™s a short walk to the Eiffel Tower and not far from other local attractions. There are shops and restaurants right around the corner and almost on every block. Itâ€™s a great centrally located hotel and I would stay here again!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
The hotel is situated in the centre near Eifel Tower
The room was small but it is written on the web
Breakfast is typical for France
You can easily walk to all attractions.
The nearest metro is Ecole Militar

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: we got scammed by an Airbnb. We walked with our tired toddlers over to the this hotel and got greeted like royalty by Zied. He immediately accommodated us and got us the best rate. our savior! He was also helpful in helping us find a place to get COVID tested for our flight back to the states. He was so kind and friendly and made what started off as a terrible vacation into a great one. They also helped us arrange transportation back to the airport. He took all the stress out of our trip. The rooms were neat and comfortable and the hotel is in a great location close to the Eiffel tower and restaurants. Thank you Zied for saving our vacation! I can't wait to come back for another visit.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: We enjoyed our stay. The staff was friendly and helpful in helping us navigate Paris. The hotel is about three minutes walk from the Eiffel Tower, 6 minute walk from the subway, and has a lot of restaurants and Shops. The rooms were beautiful and they were VERY, VERY clean, which is the most important thing to me when I travel. I'd recommend to anyone who is looking for a nice, clean hotel that's not right in the middle of all of the tourist traffic.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: We booked this hotel as it was very close to the Eiffel Tower and could accommodate our family of 3. The room was VERY small, but typical of most non-chain European hotels. Really no complaints. We parked our car at a garage several blocks away as there is no drivable road in front of the hotel.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
I was in Paris at the very beginning of the Covid 19 shut down. My original hotel closed down, but Hotel de la Paix rescued me, and with all of the grace and welcome hospitality that could be offered.

This is a gem of a small hotel in the desired 7th. It's close to the Metro, Rue Clar and the Eiffel Tower. Feeling recently remodeled, the decor was very modern and comfortable.

But more than anything else in a very stressful time, the staff was gracious and kind and accommodating, offering a refuge during the onset of the shutdown.

Under different circumstances, this location and property would be a gem. In the midst of a once in a lifetime trauma, it was a lifesaver.

Merci!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
We stayed here for 3 night last weekend.
The reason we chose this hotel was the location, close to Eiffel, hop on hop off bus and cruise and the fact that they have a patio outside the room.

You cant go wrong with this hotel.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Stayed for two nights. Loved this little hotel! Room was nice! In city center, close to the Eiffel Tower, Metro, bus routes, cafes, pastry shops, the river. Staff was amazing and always helpful! Would gladly stay again!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The overall stay was excellent. We would recommend the Hotel. The Staff was excellent and responsive. The breakfast was good. The room was clean and fresh. The television service (i.e. the cable) should be improved.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This hotel is near to Eiffel Tower and the rooms are very clean . The staff is very helpful and friendly. The only thing is that during winter they dont turn on the A/C. Thats ok for rooms on second floor or above because if you want you can open the windows during the night. But we stayed on first floor and couldnt open the window because it faced the mini indoor patio. I sweat a lot and the A/C was off.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The customer service was nothing but perfect, very friendly and helpful staff.(Ghani) was so kind to us and made us feel at home, gave us instructions on where to go and how to get there. Highly recommended

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This was perfect, took my family here and the loved it. Lots to do nearby and the concierge was amazing and kind. Would definitely come back. The Eiffel tower was walking distance and lots of shops and good restaurants.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Three of us enjoyed the hotel and being an easy walk from the Eiffel Tower. Two of us had to keep our suitcases closed and upright (typical!!), however we considered this a small inconvenience. Staff were very friendly and helpful. Also being near a train stop meant getting around Paris was easy.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
I can see the Eiffel Tower in 5 minutes' walk.
It was nice to take a walk looking at the Eiffel Tower every day.
The staff was friendly and well positioned.
But the bathroom sink was too small and uncomfortable.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The hotel location was great. Zied was great. He got us into a restaurant that we probably would not have gotten in by ourselves. Fabulous recommendation. After our son got stuck in the elevator when we were checking out, he got the repair company there fast. Our 12 year old was out within 40 minutes.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Hotel located within walking distance to Eiffel Tower and Big Bus stop. Many small restaurants around. Rooms are very tiny, as well the bathrooms, but very clean and well maintained. Small dinning area in the basement, where you can have nice breakfast. Staff very friendly and helpful.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The hotel is ideally situated near the Tour Eiffel. The location is safe and visitors can walk out at night to see the Eiffel Tower. It is also a short walk to the Seine but the concierge was so accommodating if asked to call a cab. There are ample restaurants and shops to see. The hotel rooms are kept spotless and well maintained. Let me recommend this cozy hotel for you.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Location, cleanliness and polite staff are common in this hotel. You can easily reach the Tour Eiffel and you have some good restaurants in the neighborhood. Moquette is very clean and there is no dust in the room. Bed is comfortable

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Hotel dela Paix was good. The location was awesome and the staff was great. It was really close to all must see attractions. Breakfast had great selection and taste yummy. The laundromat was just around the corner. Really convenient. I definitely recommend.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This was a great hotel. We loved the staff and everything about it. We will return! Our breakfast was very fresh every morning and the staff was so friendly. We could walk to the Eiffel Tower in less than 10 minutes. Thank you!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Close to Eiffel Tower and other areas. Quiet, small street. Staff was excellent. If you are not used to or like smaller hotels and rooms or if you are on the bigger/taller size don't book you'll be a bit uncomfortable. For people wanting to experience the real Paris and Europe and don't mind the smaller rooms,it is excellent.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The hotel staff is Awesome. The location of the hotel is Great, it's a walking distance to most prominent attractions in Paris. Stylish finish in the room we stayed. We loved it. I recommend this hotel.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Stayed for 1 night on 17th Dec 2019. Found the place close from Effiel tower and friendly staff. Place is very neat and clean

Many cafes and restaurants around, safe area to venture around at night. Many souvenir shops, pharmacy and essentials easily available at walking distance

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This is my second time staying with this hotel this year. Both times now I've had a great experience with them. The hotel is clean and modern, rooms are a good size (rooms in Paris are often small) , staff are brilliant, especially if you don't speak great French. The staff were accommodating, friendly and always happy to help. The hotel is a short distance from the metro, and very close to plenty of great restaurants, cafÃ©s and bakeries. Also, minutes from the Eiffel Tower.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: My family and I stayed here for a few days. Our stay was very pleasant and the location was great. The staff is very friendly and the complex is very clean. Close to restaurants, boutiques and a few minutes from the Eiffel Tower. Great place to stay

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Out little family will definitely come back and stay here again! The location is perfect and the place is cozy and nice. We recommend the hotel and we are planning to come back with other family members!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: this place is in nice, quiet environment, 5 min walk from Eifel tower, rooms are a bit small, but clean and comfortable, staff is very helpful and polite, speaking good English, price a bit higher, but we are in Paris

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This hotel was just a short walk away from the Eiffel Tower and the Seine! The hotel itself was very clean, and both of the staff members I interacted with were very helpful. Just be aware that the elevator is very small, so you may need to take multiple trips if you have more than one suitcase with you. I would definitely stay again!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Great location 10 mins walk to Eifel tower. 5 mins walk to metro, safe neighborhood, very friendly staff, very clean and comfortable. i purchased breakfast in advance. Breakfast could be better but it was ok. I will definitely come back next time.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The hotel is very nice and the location is perfect. Also the staff is very nice and friendly and the breakfast is good. But the rooms are very very small. The hotel is also not cheap. So a nice hotel for one night for one person.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
Good location to walk to metro and Eiffel
Tower, rooms were small, but pleasant and clean and staff were good and friendly and helpful. Would only want to stay for a short time as very small and no bath.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Lovely hotel, friendly staff, very clean rooms. Hotel staff was very accommodating, helped me to book bus ticket to my next destination as well as helped with booking the shuttle back to the airport. Room was comfortable and warm. WiFi was good too.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The staff is very attentive to anything you may need. The proximity to not only the Eiffel Tower but also to bus and metro lines was great. Lots of bistros, cafes and patisseries/brasseries in the area. Very pleasant. Area felt safe. We walked everywhere at all times of day and night with no problems. Our only complaint if we have one would be the size of the room. It could not have been more than 11ft by 11ft. We could open a smaller suitcase on the baggage stand but then the bathroom door would not open completely. Even if you were willing to put your open suitcase on the floor you could not. The distance between the bed and the walls on either side was inadequate for that. Now, all the rooms may not be that small. We were on the first floor, room #3 with immediate proximity to the lobby and we had a small table and chairs on the shared patio with another room. We did not use it though because we were there in November. Not having to use the elevator to come and go was another plus for that room and it was very quiet.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: We already stayed at the hotel 6 or 7 times, all was excellent, service, meal, bed, toilets, room, breakfast (they even provided us with breakfast at 6:15 am as we were harrying for airport), so we were fully satisfied

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews:
I love the hotel. It is small, so don't expect huge room for the price you pay. The hotel's room in Paris are small. I had been stay in a smaller room before in Paris. The staff are very friendly & helpful. The location has many good restaurant surrounding the hotel. I like cafe constant & de Mar. There is a store selling very good pate and cheese close by hotel. Few block to Eiffel Tower and many other sightseeing . There is cafe in the corner and middle of all the road that is close to Eiffel Tower is a great place for people watching, but the waiters can be very aggressive to get the customer.

Con: The room is small, but very functional. The bathroom is small and shower is small, but it is ok for us, but if a big guy then it can be a problem. The temperature is control by the hotel people (main setting), you can not control in the roomm

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Hotel is in the great location near public transports, nice restaurants and market. As we had only 1 night in Paris and we wanted to do boat trip at night so we decided to stay near Eiffle tower and the pier for boat trip which is about 10 minutes safe and pleasant walk at night from and back to the hotel. I stayed in a different hotel on the same street before. But it was much better experience this time. As we paid mostly for the location, the rooms of the hotels in the area will not be spacious but cosy. However, the hotel made us feel value for money with their high standard room decors and furnitures, cleanliness, comfortable even sofar bed, safe box with universal socket on the safe box door (Sadly, we spotted that when we're about to leave.) and electric kettle (apparently NOT all the hotels in the area with the same number of stars have it available, tea/ coffee in bed is the must!). In addition to that, the choice of 2 single or double bed in a triple room (the 3rd bed was a sofa bed) was handy and that was why we choose this hotel as we are 3 friends who prefered to have our own separate bed in 1 room. Staffs were welcoming, friendly and well English spoken. He had a Paris map with the hotel location and attractions ready for us without asking. We left out 1 star for any room of improvement and the milk that were missing from our tea and coffee making tray.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: While my single room was quite small, it ticked all the boxes. Everything was clean and comfortable. The staff was friendly and accommodating. Metro was very close so I could get around the city very easily. The area was safe and had all the conveniences that I needed.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: This small but cozy and intimate hotel n Paris was perfect for our 4-night stay. We arrived at 11am and our room was ready even though check-in was at 2pm. Very accommodating and friendly staff. The room was small but very comfortable. Itâ€™s a fabulous location on a very lovely Quiet Parisienne Street close to the Eiffel Tower and walking distance to a lot of tourist attractions, metro stops, museums and restaurants. Ihigly recommend this place for singles or couples.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Location and room were excellent but our room key worked for a different room when we accidentally went to the wrong room, while people were in there so we were a bit paranoid someone else could come into our room in the night and we put a do not disturb sign on the door throughout the day but our room was entered and stuff was moved around after we asked it not to be

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Modern, comfortable room on a charming street. Hotel staff very welcoming and helpful. Quick walk to the Eiffel Tower, many restaurants and metro stations. Big plus for me was the dark curtains that completely blocked out the sun in the morning!

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: Staff very friendly & helpful. Got us into our room early since we had arrived after a red eye from the US. Great location. Breakfast was good. We had a room on the ground floor that was small but very clean. The street was nice & quiet

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: I arrived late at night as a long layover in Paris. The staff was friendly, the bed was comfortable and the location was fantastic. I was able to see the Eiffel Tower before going back to the airport.

hotel: Hotel de la Paix Tour Eiffel
reviews: The staff is wonderful! One of our traveling companions left behind her binder with tickets in it and the manager chased us down to return it to her. Location is great. Rooms are smaller than usual for Europe. Location was good for walking around Eiffel Tower area.
